The paper deals with the problem of finding optimal weights for a neural network, which is a common topic in the field of neural networks and machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the use of memristor-based neuromorphic microchip designs, which falls under the category of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). The problem of finding optimal weights can also be considered a sub-topic of optimization, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of quadratic programming and the proof of NP-hardness suggest a connection to theoretical computer science, specifically in the areas of approximation algorithms and complexity theory, which fall under the categories of cs.AR (Architecture) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
